## Animation Conventions

Use `flutter_animate` for entrance animations. Use `AnimatedContainer` (200–250ms) for state changes.

```dart
// List item entrance — staggered
.animate().fadeIn(delay: Duration(milliseconds: i * 50), duration: 300.ms)

// Section entrance
.animate().fadeIn(duration: 400.ms)

// Hero / onboarding entrance
.animate().fadeIn(delay: 300.ms, duration: 600.ms).slideY(begin: 0.3)

// Scale bounce (success states, confetti moments)
ScaleTransition(scale: CurvedAnimation(parent: ctrl, curve: Curves.elasticOut))
```

Confetti: `ConfettiController(duration: ~1600ms)`, explosive blast, colours `[primary, accent, secondary, white]`, 40–50 particles, gravity 0.2–0.25.

Progress dots (animated): active dot widens to 20px, inactive = 6px, 250ms `AnimatedContainer`.

---

## Navigation

- **`context.go()`** — tab switches, auth redirects, deep links with query params
- **`context.push()`** — sub-screens (settings, detail views, modals via router)
- **`context.pop()`** — back from pushed screens
- Deep link to specific tab: `/mindset?tab=1` (MindsetScreen reads `GoRouterState.uri.queryParameters['tab']`)
- No custom route transitions — use default Material platform transitions

---

## Copy & Strings

Always use `AppStrings.*` constants. Never hardcode user-facing strings directly in widgets. Add new strings to `lib/core/constants/app_strings.dart`.

